title: Requires non-toxic pest management and fertilization of state and municipal park lands
summary: Requires non-toxic pest management and fertilization of municipal park lands and lands within the custody and control of the office of parks, recreation and historic preservation; creates a state pest management committee; requires such office and municipalities to develop pest management plans.
lawSection: Parks, Recreation and Historic Preservation Law
actClause: AN ACT to amend the parks, recreation and historic preservation law and the general municipal law, in relation to non-toxic pest management and fertilization of park lands
